dcterms:description: The CAMELS dataset includes catchment attributes and meteorological data for 671 basins, selected for their low anthropogenic impacts, and is used for large-sample hydrology studies.
dcterms:title: CAMELS Dataset

dcterms:creator: A. W. Wood

dcterms:description: The Maurer Forcings dataset provides long-range experimental hydrologic forecasting data for the eastern United States, including daily cumulative precipitation and temperature data.
dcterms:title: Maurer Forcings

dcterms:description: Benchmark models include various hydrological models such as SAC-SMA, VIC, FUSE, HBV, and mHM, which are used for comparison in hydrological modeling studies.
dcterms:title: Benchmark Models (SAC-SMA, VIC, FUSE, HBV, mHM)
